english:
  title: Admonition to the Rooster
  author: Lee Che-hyun
  language: eng
  text: |-
    It crows without missing its time,
    Fights without yielding its pride.
    Pecking at filth to grow fat,
    It hastens its own offering to the blade.
  footnotes:
    - This poem is a satirical commentary using the rooster as an allegory for human behavior and folly. The rooster's virtues—punctuality and courage—become instruments of its own demise through gluttony and pride.
